gomodel:SYNGO_2510  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Electron micrographs showing immunoperoxidase labeling for the D1 receptor within the ICMs\"\n- \"The D1R was most commonly found within spines (Fig. 5a, b) that typically received asymmetric synaptic inputs from unlabeled terminals. In some instances, D1R-labeled spines were seen to emerge from parent dendrites that were devoid of D1R labeling (Fig. 5c). The D1R was less commonly present within dendrites (Fig. 5d) or axon terminals (Fig. 5e).\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Eleven adult male Spraque Dawley rats weighing 300-400 g were used in this study.\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2510" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

